    "title": "addnode RPC call should return success/failure indicator",
    "body": "Calling `bitcoin-cli addnode i-am-not-an-address onetry` fails immediately and permanently, but does not give any indication that happened. Having `addnode .. onetry` instead block and return either an error or indicate the peer id of the new connection would probably be better. See also https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/19315#pullrequestreview-528084558",
